   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Sixty CHRIST CRUCIFIED Scripture: 1 Cor 1:23 Who is Christ?</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>He is the Son of God and also God Himself.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>He came to be a man whose name is Jesus.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>He came as a man in order to be our Savior.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Why was Christ crucified?</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>He was crucified in order to accomplish God s way of salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>He was crucified to remove the sins of man.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>He was crucified in order to release His life.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Christ crucified Christ is the Savior; the cross is the means of salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Therefore, Christ crucified is the Savior who accomplished the way of salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Although He was Christ crucified, today He is Christ resurrected!</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>He is no longer on the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>He is not only the Savior who accomplished the way of salvation, but He is living to impart His saving life into man.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>How to receive Christ</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
